#  Report

## Project Name
Library Management System

## Project Overview
The Library Management System is a web-based application that allows users to log in, search for books, borrow books, and return borrowed books. The system is designed as a simple Minimum Viable Product (MVP) focusing on core library operations.

## Quality Attributes

### 1. Usability
The system should be easy to use and understand. Users should be able to search, borrow, and return books without difficulty.

### 2. Reliability
The system should correctly update book status when books are borrowed or returned to ensure accurate information.

### 3. Security
The system should protect user information and prevent unauthorized access to library data.

## Possible Quality Risk

Unauthorized access may allow users to view or modify information without permission.

## Risk Mitigation

The system should implement user authentication and validate user actions before allowing changes to data.

## Conclusion

The Library Management System focuses on usability, reliability, and security as its primary quality attributes. Addressing these attributes helps ensure a useful and dependable application for users.
